1
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,240
Go on, hit me!

2
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,040
Hit me!

3
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:35,880
Go ahead, hit me!

4
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:37,280
He hit Xiao Yu!

5
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:38,240
I was disciplining him!

6
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:39,240
You, disciplining him?

7
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,680
How old are you?

8
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:41,920
You're a senior master!

9
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:43,680
Why stoop to his level?

10
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,880
Masters, show's over.

11
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:47,440
Everyone, back to the workshop.

12
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,520
Nothing to see here, move along.

13
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:49,040
Everyone, head back.

14
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:49,440
Beanpole.

15
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:50,000
Get back, get back.

16
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:50,520
You too, get back.

17
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,440
Go, go, go.

18
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:51,880
Look at him.

19
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:52,280
Come on, Master Ye.

20
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,000
Head back now, go on.

21
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:53,400
Back to work, back to work.

22
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,160
Go, hurry up.

23
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:20,680
What's wrong?

24
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:22,240
Old Xuan

25
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:25,960
I'm tired

26
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:29,880
So tired

27
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:36,000
Let's sell the factory

28
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,080
If someone wants it

29
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,560
just give it to them

30
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:46,440
If no one wants it, we'll just close down

31
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,560
Either way, the Xuan family workers

32
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:51,200
will be treasured wherever they go

33
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,160
Why are you saying all this?

34
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,640
Because I'm worn out

35
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:04,560
I can't keep going anymore

36
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,920
Old Xuan, just think about it

37
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:11,000
After all these decades together

38
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:12,560
I...

39
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:15,280
I can't recall ever spending a single day

40
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,280
of happiness with you

41
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,000
Just look

42
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:24,200
Other women my age

43
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,440
either go hiking

44
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:30,720
or enjoy the sights

45
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,800
And me?

46
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,200
Every day the moment I open my eyes

47
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,720
I'm busy non-stop

48
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:38,880
without even knowing what I'm busy with

49
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,920
Just worrying if there are orders today

50
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,800
or orders tomorrow

51
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,520
If there are no orders

52
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:48,960
how am I going to pay the workers?

53
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,080
I'm just too tired

54
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:56,680
I just don't want to do it anymore

55
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,880
And I don't want this factory

56
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:02,800
to drag me down for the rest of my life

57
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,120
Alright, alright

58
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,920
Don't say these things

59
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:13,960
It's all my fault

60
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,360
My fault for not doing better

61
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:19,519
For making you suffer alongside me

62
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,519
Enough, enough. After all these decades

63
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:23,200
you only have those same two lines

64
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,080
and they don't help at all

65
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,360
I don't want to hear them anymore

66
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,040
Think back then

67
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,680
I ignored Master's objections

68
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:31,200
and insisted on running this mechanical paper mill

69
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,600
just because mechanical paper makes good money

70
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,360
Isn't that the same as your Xuan Paper Cultural Creative Products

71
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,640
that you're doing now?

72
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,480
If you put it that way

73
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,960
then I can understand a little

74
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:41,360
Master didn't understand

75
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:43,720
So many people in Peach Blossom Town didn't understand back then

76
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:44,800
What didn't they call me?

77
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,880
Heartless

78
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,120
Ungrateful

79
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,200
What else?

80
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,480
Betraying my master's house, right?

81
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,520
Honestly, I didn't care what they said

82
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:55,000
What I cared about most was what Master and his wife

83
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,120
were thinking

84
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,360
I came to the Xuan family at age ten

85
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,000
It was that elderly couple

86
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,520
who raised me with their own hands

87
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,120
Fed me, gave me a place to sleep

88
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,800
and taught me the craft

89
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,240
My master, when out in public

90
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,000
never called me his apprentice

91
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,680
He always said

92
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:15,200
"Little Min is half a son to me"

93
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,360
As the old saying goes

94
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,560
A teacher for a day is a father for a lifetime

95
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:27,320
My biggest wish right now

96
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:29,360
is to plug up that hole as soon as possible

97
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:32,200
so I can return to the Xuan family soon

98
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,720
and serve those two elders in their old age

99
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,360
Chairman, ever since we launched

100
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:33,320
the Xuan paper notebook product line,

101
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:34,080
within just one month,

102
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:36,240
our volume has surged by 60 percent.

103
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,000
Right now, both our production lines

104
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:41,240
are running full tilt on the notebook orders.

105
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,080
Yuqing, pull up the production records

106
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:43,920
for the Chairman to review.

107
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:44,680
Right away.

108
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:50,000
This little notebook

109
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,560
is actually quite interesting.

110
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:53,680
Is this

111
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,200
designed by that young man you mentioned?

112
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,880
Yes, this young man,

113
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:59,680
I think he has tremendous potential.

114
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:00,720
He graduated from BJUT,

115
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,680
the Arts and Crafts Design Department.

116
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,360
After coming back, he's been wholly devoted

117
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,760
to Xuan Paper Cultural Creative Products.

118
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,680
I was just about to report to you,

119
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:09,320
I want to broker a deal between him and Dayazhai

120
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:10,720
for an ongoing exclusive partnership.

121
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:10,800
An ongoing exclusive partnership.

122
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,800
Let's discuss it in your office.

123
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,480
Come.

124
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:23,760
Chairman, our traditional business,

125
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:25,640
thread-bound classics and fine calligraphy paper,

126
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:27,240
has pretty much reached its limit.

127
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:30,360
Honestly, the market is just too small.

128
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:33,360
A major breakthrough would be extremely difficult.

129
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,120
But this Xuan Yan,

130
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,520
many of his designs,

131
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,200
I really like them.

132
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:40,560
I believe Xuan Paper Cultural Creative Products

133
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,320
will have an even bigger market ahead.

134
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,320
And there's one thing that's especially interesting.

135
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,760
This Xuan Yan,

136
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:49,240
he has extremely high standards for quality control.

137
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:51,440
That reminds me a lot of you back when

138
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:53,560
you worked on the Complete Library of the Four Treasuries.

139
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,520
A relentless perfectionist.

140
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:02,320
You mean to make adjustments

141
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:05,920
to the Peach Blossom Town branch's direction.

142
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,680
This involves the whole group's strategy.

143
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:12,760
We must be cautious.

144
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,080
I'll think it over.

145
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,880
Chairman, you should steer the ship.

146
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,760
And President Xin,

147
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:21,200
let me interrupt for a moment.

148
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:23,880
About the Xuan paper notebook,

149
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:26,200
the design fee you agreed on with Xuan Yan,

150
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:28,000
the cut is ten percent.

151
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:30,880
Ten percent of the total order amount.

152
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:31,600
Is that right?

153
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,320
Yes.

154
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:36,520
That seems a bit unreasonable to me.

155
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,000
How is it unreasonable?

156
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:41,280
Manager Huang.

157
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:42,880
President Xin,

158
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:45,520
finance just ran the numbers.

159
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:49,240
The cost of this Xuan paper notebook is very high.

160
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:52,120
Net profit comes out to less than thirty percent.

161
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:54,320
Our whole factory works themselves to the bone,

162
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:55,760
and the designer lies at home

163
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:57,200
earning more than we do.

164
00:08:57,760 --> 00:09:00,320
That hardly seems reasonable.

165
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,920
As the business expands and grows,

166
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:05,120
costs will naturally come down.

167
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:07,360
Talent is the core driving force.

168
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,920
Without talent backing you up,

169
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:11,680
no matter how clear your books are, it's zero.

170
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,680
Don't misunderstand, President Xin.

171
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,640
We're not saying we don't need talent.

172
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,680
I just feel that

173
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:18,440
this Xuan Yan

174
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:21,320
should take ten percent of the profit.

175
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,760
That would be more appropriate.

176
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:23,640
Right?

177
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:25,440
If we open the gates this wide from the start,

178
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:27,520
how can we cooperate or negotiate later?

179
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,680
Great deeds don't dwell on trivial details.

180
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:33,200
Nitpicking won't get you far.

181
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,560
Chairman, you see?

182
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:37,120
Xin Ran is a general manager.

183
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,440
She handles production and operations all at once.

184
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:42,120
How can she ignore costs and profits?

185
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:43,520
I'm looking at the big picture.

186
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,520
Not squeezing a towel from an employee,

187
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,400
nor snatching scrap cardboard

188
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,760
from the guard to sell it myself.

189
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:53,240
What I'm calculating is the company's third-quarter

190
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,880
total revenue and net profit.

191
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:57,080
How to grow it to twenty-five percent,

192
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:59,240
whether next year we can exceed fifty percent,

193
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:01,120
or even surpass one hundred percent.

194
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,400
That's all I'm calculating.

195
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,280
Old Zhang has a point.

196
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:09,600
I know you have your reasons, Xin Ran.

197
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,880
But here's my suggestion.

198
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:15,520
Push down the cut a bit more,

199
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:16,960
and pay him at year-end.

200
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:19,160
After all, this sum

201
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,600
is no small amount.

202
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:23,720
It'll ease your cash flow.

203
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:26,880
I understand, Chairman.

204
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,760
But the contract between us

205
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:30,120
wasn't signed that way.

206
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,120
This Xuan Yan,

207
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,600
no matter how talented,

208
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:41,240
is still a young man seeking opportunities.

209
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:42,880
And you,

210
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,720
you must know exactly where you stand.

211
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:47,160
You're the client.

212
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,760
You must hold control and initiative

213
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:51,400
firmly in your own hands.

214
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:56,400
There's an old Chinese saying:

215
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:58,520
Kindness cannot command an army.

216
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,760
As a company leader,

217
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:03,040
you can't rely solely on goodwill.

218
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:05,880
Not everyone knows how to be grateful.

219
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,600
At critical moments, you must be decisive.

220
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,880
Never show mercy.

221
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:23,520
Fine, I can do as you say.

222
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:26,640
But there's something

223
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:30,160
I want to say upfront.

224
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:31,640
You sent me here

225
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:35,280
when Peach Blossom Town was a total mess.

226
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,760
That's when you assigned me.

227
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:40,600
Now the company's sorted out, back on track.

228
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:43,120
And we started turning a profit last year.

229
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:48,120
Chairman, you know me.

230
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:50,360
I have my own ambitions too.

231
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:53,960
If you just want a head steward,

232
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,040
you can pick someone else.

233
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,080
Me being here alone

234
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:58,880
wouldn't mean anything.

235
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:01,240
Since you chose to trust me,

236
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:04,360
you should give me more authority and room.

237
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,960
I believe Xuan Paper Cultural Creative Products

238
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:09,360
will open up new horizons for the group.

239
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:13,280
But I need your complete trust and support.

240
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:20,760
If I didn't trust you,

241
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,880
would I have put you in this position?

242
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:26,840
On hiring, on spending,

243
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,720
I've never interfered with you, right?

244
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:29,360
Am I right?

245
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,480
And that's something I've always

246
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,760
been especially grateful to you for.

247
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:33,480
Good. Let's leave it there.

248
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:34,840
Anything more is just nonsense.

249
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:35,960
I'll emphasize just one thing.

250
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:37,680
This year's profit margin

251
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:39,520
must exceed last year's by 50 percent.

252
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:41,120
Next year, double it. Can you do it?

253
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:46,560
Yes.

254
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,360
Good.

255
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:49,160
I'll be waiting to celebrate your success.

256
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:12,240
Hello, Mom. What's up?

257
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:44,400
Master.

258
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:46,400
This is a real treasure.

259
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,360
Look at this craftsmanship.

260
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:01,640
Uncle.

261
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:04,120
Lin Yiran.

262
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:12,640
Wait, Mom.

263
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,280
Everything's laid out.

264
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,640
Are you pawning the family assets?

265
00:14:18,040 --> 00:14:20,760
Xuan Yan, don't talk nonsense.

266
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:26,760
I, Xuan Yongnian, am incompetent.

267
00:14:27,520 --> 00:14:29,240
For things to come to this,

268
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:31,520
I have no choice but to pawn it all.

269
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:37,000
These treasures have been in the Xuan family for centuries.

270
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:39,520
Now they've passed to me, Xuan Yongnian,

271
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:42,760
and I couldn't even maintain them.

272
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:46,360
And the next generation refuses to carry on

273
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,880
the family business.

274
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,000
What else can I do?

275
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:52,240
There's no point keeping them.

276
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:53,240
Might as well

277
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,520
just sell them off.

278
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:59,640
Selling them will bring in some money.

279
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:03,880
With that, the factory can hold on a bit longer.

280
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,760
If we really can't keep going,

281
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,840
then we'll all have to go our separate ways.

282
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:10,880
Nothing can be done.

283
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:13,240
Old-timer, Zhang Du.

284
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:16,520
Look around, see who's out there.

285
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,160
Find someone reliable

286
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:19,480
to give them to.

287
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:22,360
Just don't let these treasures go to waste.

288
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:23,840
Yongnian.

289
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:27,120
These are the Xuan family's roots.

290
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:28,880
If you sell them all, then we...

291
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,760
Master, don't be so hasty.

292
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:32,600
The factory hasn't reached its end yet.

293
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:34,960
I'll go reach out to bosses I know.

294
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:37,640
Partnership investments are another path, right?

295
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:40,000
We still have plenty of paper in the warehouse.

296
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,840
I'll go out and sell it myself.

297
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,760
We can definitely keep going.

298
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:44,960
Xuan Yan.

299
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,760
You're a clever one.

300
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:47,960
Think of something for your father.

301
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,360
Is there any other way out?

302
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:50,840
Don't count on him.

303
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:53,120
He's useless.

304
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:56,160
Then tell me,

305
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:58,360
what would count as being useful to you?

306
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:01,000
Go to the factory and do sheet forming like you?

307
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:02,760
Would that make money?

308
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:04,760
Would that keep the factory running?

309
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,360
Is that what you call being useful?

310
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:07,720
Dad.

311
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:11,000
If you really sell all these things,

312
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:14,000
how will you face our ancestors?

313
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:18,360
Oh, so you do think of the ancestors?

314
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,960
Thirty-five generations of the Xuan family.

315
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:24,840
If we'd had a "genius" like you sooner,

316
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:27,720
I wouldn't be the one disgracing our ancestors.

317
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:30,280
You're right. It's all my fault.

318
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:34,640
Uncle Xuan, it shouldn't come to selling these.

319
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:38,160
These are thousand-year-old Xuan family heirlooms.

320
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:39,520
We can't sell them.

321
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:40,760
And Xuan Yan,

322
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:44,480
making Xuan paper and developing cultural products

323
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,640
aren't actually in conflict.

324
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:47,000
You're capable.

325
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,640
I believe in your hands, the Xuan family

326
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:50,120
will definitely thrive.

327
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:52,480
The government will work with you on solutions, too.

328
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:54,240
We'll protect the intangible heritage together.

329
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:55,240
Yes, yes.

330
00:16:55,240 --> 00:16:57,000
You should be saying this to my dad.

331
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:57,920
Son.

332
00:16:58,240 --> 00:17:00,120
Just listen to Miss Lin.

333
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:02,120
If you young people work together,

334
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:05,480
with fresh minds and new ideas, you'll do great.

335
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:17,480
Wait, why are you all

336
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,119
pointing your guns at me?

337
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:23,280
Isn't Dad the one selling off the family assets?

338
00:17:23,599 --> 00:17:24,400
Yes.

339
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:25,640
But our Xuan family right now

340
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:27,160
has hit a dead end.

341
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,760
Don't you have any stance on this?

342
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,520
What stance could I have, Mom?

343
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:32,600
You know this family best, right?

344
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:34,240
Dad acts on every whim he gets.

345
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:36,360
Whatever he wants to do, right or wrong,

346
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:37,640
we all have to carry it out.

347
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:39,720
We all have to do as he says, right?

348
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:41,000
If he wants to sell, then sell.

349
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:44,000
Am I sick? Did I take the wrong pills?

350
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:46,240
Selling our ancestors' things just like that?

351
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:48,160
Do you have any sense at all?

352
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:51,360
Can he even hear reason?

353
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:54,520
If he could've heard reason earlier,

354
00:17:54,520 --> 00:17:57,480
things wouldn't have come to this point today.

355
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:07,800
Dad.

356
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:09,000
I remember our family

357
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:11,280
also has Mi Fu's calligraphy and Bada Shanren's paintings.

358
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:13,120
Take them all out, sell them all.

359
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:15,240
That way, I can go from second-gen paper heir

360
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,480
to second-gen rich kid in one leap.

361
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:16,840
You scoundrel!

362
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:19,120
Xuan Yan, what nonsense are you spouting?

363
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:20,760
Dad, think it through.

364
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:22,600
Are you selling or not?

365
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:24,360
If you're selling, I'll help find buyers.

366
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:25,880
Let's sell high, don't sell at a loss.

367
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:26,600
Right?

368
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:31,040
Yongnian, we can't be foolish about this.

369
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:32,280
That's right, Master.

370
00:18:36,560 --> 00:18:38,040
Wait, that's the attitude you're taking?

371
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:39,320
We can't even keep going anymore.

372
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:40,720
Keep going with what?

373
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:49,760
Sell it all.

374
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:53,000
The Xuan family business,

375
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:55,760
and the Xuan ancestors' honor too,

376
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,760
sell them all together.

377
00:18:58,240 --> 00:18:59,600
Now that would be satisfying.

378
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:14,040
Auntie.

379
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:18,320
Auntie.

380
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:30,240
I once heard my father mention

381
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:34,320
their family has 50 or 60 ancient literati paintings.

382
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:37,320
Just one Mi Fu calligraphy, how much is that worth?

383
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:38,760
Old Ren.

384
00:19:39,560 --> 00:19:41,720
His are all practice pieces,

385
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:43,320
nothing compared to genuine masterpieces.

386
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:44,280
Not worth much.

387
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,120
But the Xuan family's paintings

388
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:48,000
weren't just casually done by the artists.

389
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,480
They were passed down from their ancestors,

390
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:52,200
all with inscriptions and seals.

391
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:52,600
Right.

392
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:53,800
Those are all top-quality items.

393
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:56,280
And all kinds of paper too.

394
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:59,480
A couple years ago, Christie's auctioned

395
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,120
a piece of paper by Weng Tonghe,

396
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,000
the size of a palm,

397
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:03,400
for over a hundred thousand.

398
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:05,640
His family has tons, all top-quality stuff.

399
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:06,040
Yes, yes, yes.

400
00:20:06,040 --> 00:20:06,760
Really?

401
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:08,600
Could it really be that much?

402
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:10,240
What do you know, you country bumpkin?

403
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,520
The Xuan family's things,

404
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:15,920
without 50 million, you can't even touch them.

405
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:16,920
How much?

406
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:18,280
Fifty million.

407
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:20,080
You really know how to flatter him.

408
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:20,880
See,

409
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,640
if you sell it right,

410
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:24,000
but if you sell it wrong,

411
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,520
it's barely worth anything.

412
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:27,880
Whatever you tell him, he won't get it.

413
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:28,800
Think about it.

414
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:31,320
This could be an opportunity.

415
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:33,880
If they're at the point of selling family heirlooms,

416
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:35,800
they must be desperate for cash.

417
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:36,520
Right?

418
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:39,080
Right, otherwise he wouldn't need to sell.

419
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,760
Anyway, I don't have the means myself.

420
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,000
Which of you has the means?

421
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,040
You all think it over.

422
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:45,080
You can't.

423
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:47,280
You all need to weigh your own worth.

424
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,120
Daydreaming without the ability,

425
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:50,440
sooner or later you'll go crazy from it.

426
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:54,760
Hold on, Old Xiao.

427
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:56,280
Xiao Min.

428
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:57,720
Gentlemen, gentlemen.

429
00:20:58,080 --> 00:20:59,360
Sit, sit. Let's have some tea first.

430
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:10,520
Xuan Yan

431
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:11,840
You're here.

432
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:14,680
What are you doing?

433
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:16,160
Just playing.

434
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:17,000
Playing?

435
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:20,320
Don't touch it.

436
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:21,280
What is this?

437
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,800
You're playing with something this valuable?

438
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:29,960
And sticking it against a pillar?

439
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:30,920
Aren't you just ruining it?

440
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:31,760
You spendthrift.

441
00:21:31,760 --> 00:21:33,800
What? I didn't use your Xuan paper.

442
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:35,200
You're out of your mind.

443
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,000
What did you want? Hurry up and say it.

444
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:38,600
Have you heard the news?

445
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:40,040
The whole town knows.

446
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:42,040
Is he really selling them?

447
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:43,520
They were passed down to my dad.

448
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:45,280
If he wants to sell, what can I do?

449
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:46,160
I can't stop him.

450
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:47,800
Is the family really so desperate

451
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:49,520
that you have to sell off the treasures?

452
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:53,000
It's a long story.

453
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:57,800
Quick, give me your account number.

454
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,640
I'll wire you a few hundred thousand.

455
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:01,080
Hold on.

456
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:03,880
Your money isn't nearly enough to fix this.

457
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,200
Then what do we do?

458
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:07,480
What my dad is holding on to...

459
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,840
It's a bottomless pit.

460
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:11,560
I can't just stand by and watch.

461
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:14,760
Don't you have an idea?

462
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,000
What idea?

463
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:20,120
Don't play dumb with me.

464
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:22,880
Aren't you tempted by our family's treasures?

465
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:27,600
Honestly,

466
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:30,120
those treasures of the Xuan family,

467
00:22:31,480 --> 00:22:32,640
anyone who sees them is tempted.

468
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:33,880
If I had the money,

469
00:22:34,120 --> 00:22:35,560
I'd buy them all up.

470
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:36,920
Not for myself,

471
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:39,680
but to safeguard the Xuan family legacy.

472
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:42,520
Whenever the old man recovers,

473
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:43,560
I'd give them back.

474
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,480
The way you say that,

475
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,800
I'm actually a little touched.

476
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,320
You really should be touched.

477
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:55,000
My loyalty to my master and the Xuan family,

478
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,400
heaven and earth can attest to it.

479
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:58,560
If I'm lying, may lightning strike me.

480
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:02,640
Fine, I'll give you a chance.

481
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:04,360
You buy them all.

482
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:06,240
Who?

483
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:07,080
You.

484
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:09,040
Me, buy them all?

485
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,920
What's wrong, Comrade Xiao Min?

486
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:17,080
Are you afraid of being struck by lightning?

487
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:20,160
I'm not afraid of lightning from the sky.

488
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:22,640
I'm afraid of the landmine you've planted.

489
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:26,120
Look at you, so clever.

490
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,720
You set a trap for your dad,

491
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:29,320
and dragged me into it.

492
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:31,680
The Xuans get the money, problem solved.

493
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:32,520
And the treasures?

494
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:34,280
They'll be safe with me.

495
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:35,960
In the end, after all this,

496
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:37,480
my money's gone.

497
00:23:37,560 --> 00:23:38,440
You're really something.

498
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:39,560
Stop jumping to conclusions, okay?

499
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,280
I'm giving you a chance to shine.

500
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:42,040
Forget it.

501
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,840
The price is way too steep.

502
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,480
You're a big boss, can't you even

503
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:46,400
do this simple math?

504
00:23:47,120 --> 00:23:48,680
How much our family treasures are worth,

505
00:23:48,680 --> 00:23:50,000
you know that yourself, right?

506
00:23:50,360 --> 00:23:52,400
Right now we're rushing to sell at a discount.

507
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:54,480
When we redeem them later,

508
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:56,200
you'll become what to my dad?

509
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:57,560
A great benefactor.

510
00:23:58,360 --> 00:23:59,800
Even if we don't redeem them,

511
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:01,440
once you resell these items,

512
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,760
how could you possibly lose money?

513
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:08,040
Could I really sell Master's treasures?

514
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:09,160
Would I dare?

515
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:11,360
By then, you'll be the one calling the shots.

516
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:15,720
I'll be honest with you.

517
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,000
I'm not afraid of anything else.

518
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:19,160
I'm just afraid that even if I sell my house and land,

519
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,440
it still won't be enough.

520
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:23,080
How much are you planning to sell for?

521
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:24,440
Let me say this upfront,

522
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:25,880
if it's too much, I can't handle it.

523
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,520
How much do you have?

524
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:30,000
I need to know your bottom line first.

525
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:31,760
How much do I have?

526
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:34,240
I have ten billion. Would you believe it?

527
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:35,000
I would.

528
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:36,080
Then let's close the deal at that price.

529
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,040
Don't lead me down the wrong path.

530
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:40,600
Answer me one question first.

531
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:43,080
Would Master agree

532
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:44,920
to sell his treasures to me?

533
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:48,120
Well,

534
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:50,040
that really would be a bit tough.

535
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:52,400
So I need to find someone else

536
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:53,840
to buy them in her name.

537
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:54,920
With your money, of course.

538
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:56,640
Who are you planning to ask?

539
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:00,960
Xin Ran.

540
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:10,200
So what do you say?

541
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,480
Think it over.

542
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:14,720
This offer won't come around again.

543
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:18,800
I heard you have Song Dynasty Jade Plate Paper.

544
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:22,520
Ming Dynasty Dew Emperor Paper and White Deer Paper,

545
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:26,000
and Qianlong's Ice Crack Plum Blossom Jade Plate Paper.

546
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:28,840
Every one of them is a paper treasure.

547
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:33,400
I'm surprised you know about Dew Emperor Paper.

548
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:38,400
According to the Jingxian Annals of Jiaqing year eleven,

549
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:42,680
Dew Emperor was offered as tribute to the court.

550
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:43,760
From this we can see

551
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:47,680
Dew Emperor circulated widely among commoners and royalty.

552
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:50,760
Jade Plate Paper was renowned in the Song Dynasty.

553
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:54,160
Smooth and white inside, soft, thin, and fine,

554
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:57,080
glossy yet sturdy, lasting without worm damage.

555
00:25:57,520 --> 00:25:58,760
Yes, yes, yes.

556
00:25:58,760 --> 00:26:00,280
Director, let's talk inside.

557
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:01,320
All right.

558
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:06,600
Yongnian.

559
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:10,760
My coming here was arranged by the factory.

560
00:26:11,240 --> 00:26:13,040
If we can talk, we'll talk.

561
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:16,240
If not, I'll just go back and report.

562
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:18,920
You're Hongxing Factory's master of sheet forming.

563
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:22,040
You entrusted your own son to me.

564
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:25,280
That shows our friendship

565
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:26,960
and your trust in me.

566
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:29,280
That's why your boss sent you.

567
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:31,280
If it were anyone else,

568
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:33,400
I wouldn't even meet with them.

569
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:35,760
Old Xuan.

570
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:37,960
Hongxing Factory, after all...

571
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:40,200
Yes, I, Xuan Yongnian, ran it poorly.

572
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:43,600
And now I'm selling off our ancestors' legacy.

573
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,280
But I don't need pity.

574
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:46,640
We're friends.

575
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,160
You come over for a couple of drinks,

576
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,120
we get together,

577
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,400
I'm thrilled.

578
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:52,000
But if it's business,

579
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:54,200
let's drop it.

580
00:26:57,760 --> 00:26:59,800
What now? We haven't even talked.

581
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:01,520
Director Liao.

582
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:03,520
Please, after you.

583
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:08,000
Yongnian.

584
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:11,840
We're already halfway in the grave.

585
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:14,520
Some things should be let go.

586
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:24,280
It was decades ago, after all.

587
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:27,200
Your Uncle Xuan always

588
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:29,320
saw his father as a role model.

589
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:31,280
But his father

590
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:34,440
refused to let your Uncle Xuan join Hongxing Factory.

591
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:37,280
He sent him to Peach Blossom Town Paper Mill instead,

592
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:40,040
hoping to lead the common folks

593
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:42,400
in learning the craft and earning a living.

594
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:46,480
So Hongxing Factory

595
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:49,080
became a dream for your Uncle Xuan,

596
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:50,240
an unresolved knot.

597
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:57,400
Then, around 1990,

598
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:59,960
the government promoted

599
00:28:00,440 --> 00:28:03,040
merging Peach Blossom Town Paper Mill with Hongxing Factory.

600
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:06,120
And so your Uncle Xuan's dream

601
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:07,680
finally came true.

602
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:09,680
You have no idea,

603
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:12,480
on his first day at the factory,

604
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:17,160
how proud and happy he was.

605
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:18,560
But within six months,

606
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:22,520
he'd offended every apprentice there.

607
00:28:23,960 --> 00:28:25,160
Do you know why?

608
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:27,560
Your uncle managed workers

609
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:31,040
by the old rules passed down from our ancestors.

610
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:33,200
But Hongxing Factory was state-owned.

611
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:34,760
They went by the system.

612
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:36,520
So conflicts arose,

613
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:39,400
and they kept getting worse.

614
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:43,720
What hurt your uncle most

615
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:48,520
was that the apprentices who had served him tea

616
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:49,920
all filed complaints against him.

617
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:52,240
And those bosses, too,

618
00:28:52,240 --> 00:28:53,840
without bothering to sort it out,

619
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:56,720
demanded your uncle apologize to his own apprentices.

620
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:59,280
Think about it, with your Uncle Xuan's temper,

621
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:01,680
how could he apologize to apprentices? Right?

622
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:05,920
I totally understand Uncle Xuan.

623
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:08,520
Since ancient times, what master ever

624
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:10,040
apologized to an apprentice?

625
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:12,800
If he apologized, how could he still be the master?

626
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:15,280
That's exactly what your Uncle Xuan thought.

627
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:19,200
So in a fit of anger,

628
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:22,240
he walked out of Hongxing Factory and quit.

629
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:24,320
And he swore that for the rest of his life,

630
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:25,920
he'd never set foot in Hongxing Factory again.

631
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:27,800
No dealings, no cooperation with them.

632
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,840
Hongxing Factory broke his heart.

633
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:37,720
Have some apple.

634
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:39,760
You poked me.

635
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:41,200
President Xin.

636
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:46,000
How did the talks go?

637
00:29:46,600 --> 00:29:49,160
A deal this big can't be closed in one go.

638
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:51,240
I've raised my offer to six million.

639
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:52,560
Six million?

640
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:54,240
What do you mean, Mr. Xiao?

641
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:55,040
Too much?

642
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:56,320
If it's too much, don't come to me.

643
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:57,680
Besides, when I'm negotiating face-to-face,

644
00:29:57,680 --> 00:29:58,600
I can't exactly consult with you.

645
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,320
Right, I...

646
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:00,720
No, Xin Ran, Xin Ran.

647
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:02,560
Brother Min just thinks you settled for too little.

648
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:03,280
Loss of face.

649
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:05,800
That's not what I meant.

650
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,080
Then what does he mean?

651
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:09,440
He might have feelings for you.

652
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:12,520
Speak properly.

653
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:14,280
He...

654
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:16,720
He thinks now that we're partners,

655
00:30:16,760 --> 00:30:17,520
we're ripping him off.

656
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:19,360
No, I...

657
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:20,000
Mr. Xiao.

658
00:30:20,120 --> 00:30:21,560
If you really think that way,

659
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:23,600
then your mindset really is a bit...

660
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:24,600
President Xin, President Xin, President Xin.

661
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:26,400
I, Xiao Min, am really not that kind of person.

662
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:29,520
Anyway, I've raised it to six million now.

663
00:30:30,360 --> 00:30:34,000
And I think the old man is a bit tempted.

664
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:40,880
That's good then.

665
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:45,160
If Master agrees, we can even add a bit more.

666
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:48,080
Now that's broadening your mindset.

667
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:56,800
Here.

668
00:30:57,320 --> 00:30:58,120
Okay.

669
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:00,480
Manager Du, have some tea.

670
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:06,240
My ancestors were also papermakers.

671
00:31:06,520 --> 00:31:07,680
Come to think of it,

672
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:11,360
we actually share the same lineage as the Xuan family.

673
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:13,760
May I ask,

674
00:31:13,800 --> 00:31:17,000
where does your family's heritage come from?

675
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:18,760
The Du family of Guangdong.

676
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:20,400
I see.

677
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:21,840
When I was little,

678
00:31:21,920 --> 00:31:24,000
I heard from the older generation

679
00:31:24,240 --> 00:31:26,920
that there was an apprentice surnamed Du from Guangdong

680
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:30,320
who learned sheet forming from my great-grandfather.

681
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:32,800
Later, he did quite well for himself,

682
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:34,760
expanding all the way to Hong Kong, China.

683
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:38,960
After the liberation, contact was lost.

684
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:43,000
That was indeed my great-grandfather, Du Qingdong.

685
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,280
I see.

686
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,280
Are you still making paper now?

687
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:49,240
It's embarrassing to say,

688
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:50,320
but no, not anymore.

689
00:31:50,760 --> 00:31:51,520
All these years,

690
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:54,520
I've been running a shipping business in Guangdong.

691
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:56,520
But for my ancestors' papermaking,

692
00:31:56,760 --> 00:31:58,720
I've always held a deep sentiment.

693
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:01,240
So, a few friends and I

694
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:03,760
opened a Xuan paper museum.

695
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:05,040
The reason I came

696
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:07,320
is that I heard you're selling off

697
00:32:07,320 --> 00:32:10,000
your ancestors' old paper and calligraphy works.

698
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:11,160
I was thinking

699
00:32:11,760 --> 00:32:14,600
they could be preserved and exhibited in the museum.

700
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:18,000
That would be a fine home for them.

701
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:22,520
What's the name of your museum?

702
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:24,840
Detian.

703
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:26,160
Detian.

704
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:28,520
If I may ask one more thing,

705
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:30,520
who did you hear it from

706
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:32,760
that the Xuan family is selling old paper and artworks?

707
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:38,400
That's not important.

708
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:42,120
Knowing the source might actually matter.

709
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:47,240
Uncle Xuan,

710
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:50,600
may I have a look at the items first?

711
00:32:50,600 --> 00:32:51,360
Sure.

712
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:52,480
Zhang Du.

713
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:55,000
Show them to Mr. Du.

714
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:57,040
Okay.

715
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:01,000
I should have you stay for a meal.

716
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:05,480
Uncle Xuan,

717
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:07,760
the price I'm offering is already quite high.

718
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,520
After all, our two families

719
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:11,280
are really one family.

720
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:14,680
I'm planning to head back the day after tomorrow.

721
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:17,520
Please give it serious consideration.

722
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:18,280
Alright.

723
00:33:18,600 --> 00:33:19,320
Where are you staying?

724
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:21,280
If it's convenient, why not stay at our place?

725
00:33:21,280 --> 00:33:21,840
No, thank you.

726
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,960
I'm at the Qingyi Hotel in the county town.

727
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,400
It's all been arranged.

728
00:33:25,400 --> 00:33:26,320
Alright, alright.

729
00:33:26,800 --> 00:33:29,480
I'll give you an answer tomorrow.

730
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:31,160
Okay.

731
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:32,240
Alright, goodbye.

732
00:33:51,160 --> 00:33:51,960
Master.

733
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:55,240
Something feels off about that guy.

734
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:58,040
His hands have clearly done sheet forming.

735
00:33:58,320 --> 00:34:00,160
Otherwise, whose hands would have calluses

736
00:34:00,160 --> 00:34:00,960
in that exact spot?

737
00:34:02,760 --> 00:34:05,200
So what if he's done sheet forming?

738
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:07,720
At the very least, he lied to you.

739
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:08,520
Lied to me?

740
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:10,480
He paid money to buy things.

741
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,840
What does it matter whether he lied or not?

742
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:30,600
I knew it was you from the sound.

743
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:32,480
You sure know your way around here.

744
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:33,920
You didn't even make an appointment.

745
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:36,199
I did make one.

746
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:38,239
When? How come I don't know?

747
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:40,520
Does my appointment have to be with you?

748
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:43,760
Wait, wait, wait.

749
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:44,639
You came here.

750
00:34:44,639 --> 00:34:46,280
If not me, then who?

751
00:34:46,679 --> 00:34:47,960
I don't see anyone over there.

752
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:48,880
Move aside.

753
00:34:49,159 --> 00:34:49,960
Yiran.

754
00:34:50,719 --> 00:34:51,520
Let's talk inside.

755
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:52,159
Come on.

756
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:54,280
What did you find out?

757
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:55,520
Here, take a look.

758
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:57,320
I did some digging.

759
00:34:57,480 --> 00:35:00,800
There is a Detian Xuan Paper Museum.

760
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:04,160
Invested in by Detian Fuming Company.

761
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:05,560
The legal rep is Bi Fuqing.

762
00:35:05,880 --> 00:35:07,520
That's all I could dig up.

763
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:10,240
Hey, what are you two talking about?

764
00:35:12,080 --> 00:35:15,000
This company is facing over twenty lawsuits.

765
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:16,640
That's not normal, right?

766
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:18,200
That's exactly what I'm saying.

767
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:19,720
Something fishy about this company.

768
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:20,880
Oh, right.

769
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:23,240
This Mr. Du you mentioned must be a partner.

770
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:23,920
Right?

771
00:35:24,480 --> 00:35:26,560
But he's not a shareholder.

772
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:29,960
You two are treating me like I'm invisible.

773
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:31,520
Do you even care?

774
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:32,680
Of course I care.

775
00:35:32,680 --> 00:35:34,040
That's our family treasure.

776
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:35,560
I have to pick a good buyer.

777
00:35:35,640 --> 00:35:36,560
This Mr. Du,

778
00:35:36,960 --> 00:35:38,680
when I shook his hand, I noticed

779
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:41,360
his hands have definitely done sheet forming.

780
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:44,440
But he insists he's a businessman, not a papermaker.

781
00:35:45,040 --> 00:35:47,840
He says the museum is just out of passion.

782
00:35:47,920 --> 00:35:49,520
But when I showed him the treasure,

783
00:35:49,720 --> 00:35:51,560
he wasn't excited at all.

784
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:53,160
The look in his eyes,

785
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:55,360
there wasn't even a spark.

786
00:35:57,440 --> 00:36:00,040
But could there be a possibility

787
00:36:00,040 --> 00:36:01,680
that since they're about to negotiate price,

788
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:02,880
he can't seem too eager?

789
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:05,720
That's possible.

790
00:36:05,760 --> 00:36:06,760
No way, no way.

791
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:07,880
I've been listening for a while now.

792
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:09,080
This guy is definitely unreliable.

793
00:36:09,080 --> 00:36:10,120
Absolutely don't sell it to him.

794
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:12,280
But Master is already tempted.

795
00:36:12,760 --> 00:36:13,640
When I left,

796
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:16,040
he was discussing it with Master's wife.

797
00:36:16,120 --> 00:36:17,920
Wait, so today there were no...

798
00:36:17,920 --> 00:36:20,120
No other bidders came?

799
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:21,320
Xin Ran came.

800
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:22,480
Right, Xin Ran came.

801
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:24,880
She offered 6 million, Mr. Du offered 10 million.

802
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:26,160
If it were you, who would you sell to?

803
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:28,520
That, that much?

804
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:30,920
Still, you can't sell to Mr. Du.

805
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:33,040
I really don't get you.

806
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,920
Mr. Du offers 10 million, no sale.

807
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:36,480
Xin Ran offers 6 million, you'd sell?

808
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:39,160
No, I mean don't sell to either.

809
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:42,040
You know what

810
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:44,520
I'm most curious about right now?

811
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:47,160
He's supposedly from Guangdong,

812
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:48,480
so how did he find out

813
00:36:48,480 --> 00:36:50,120
that we have a treasure here?

814
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:51,840
That's what I'm saying.

815
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:53,320
There's definitely something fishy.

816
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:54,600
We can't let him succeed.

817
00:36:54,800 --> 00:36:56,320
I'm afraid it'll be too late.

818
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:56,600
What's wrong?

819
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:58,000
If Master agrees,

820
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:59,280
they'll sign tomorrow.

821
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:02,760
That's a real problem.

822
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:18,080
Old Xuan

823
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:21,560
You're really selling?

824
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:26,880
Uncle Xuan, do you want to think it over?

825
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:29,760
No more thinking.

826
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:38,440
If you don't need me, I'll be going.

827
00:38:38,600 --> 00:38:39,600
Wait a moment.

828
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:41,720
Sit down first.

829
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:45,160
We're selling the Xuan family heirloom.

830
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,160
You're part of the Xuan family.

831
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:49,800
You have to sign it too.

832
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:53,240
Who am I to sign?

833
00:38:53,880 --> 00:38:55,760
Isn't this house still your call?

834
00:38:55,880 --> 00:38:57,280
You still have to sign.

835
00:38:57,280 --> 00:38:59,720
Without your consent, how can we sell?

836
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:01,880
You're the father, you sign first.

837
00:39:02,520 --> 00:39:03,440
If you don't sign,

838
00:39:04,120 --> 00:39:05,120
then I won't sign either.

839
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:06,280
Enough.

840
00:39:06,640 --> 00:39:09,920
At a time like this, father and son still bickering?

841
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:14,520
Mr. Xuan,

842
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:18,280
wasn't I the one who negotiated with you first?

843
00:39:18,520 --> 00:39:22,240
Now suddenly you want to sign with someone else?

844
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:23,920
In business,

845
00:39:23,920 --> 00:39:26,560
everyone wants to land a good price.

846
00:39:27,080 --> 00:39:28,960
That's only human nature.

847
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:29,800
I understand.

848
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:32,640
But my initial offer of six million

849
00:39:32,640 --> 00:39:34,080
was just a preliminary intent.

850
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:36,000
If you feel the price isn't right,

851
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:37,600
we can keep negotiating.

852
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:50,320
This gentleman,

853
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:54,080
I'd like to know what your offer is.

854
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:57,680
I'm offering ten million.

855
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:11,520
Mr. Xuan,

856
00:40:12,520 --> 00:40:16,120
I can also match that ten-million offer.

857
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:17,880
Oh my goodness.

858
00:40:18,240 --> 00:40:19,320
Where would I get ten million?

859
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:21,320
There's a first-come, first-served order.

860
00:40:21,360 --> 00:40:24,240
Since I was the first to negotiate with you,

861
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:26,880
would you consider giving us another chance?

862
00:40:27,520 --> 00:40:28,320
Uncle Xuan,

863
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:31,600
I don't care when you talked to her.

864
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:33,480
The bottom line is, no deal was made.

865
00:40:33,800 --> 00:40:37,240
Ten million was the price we agreed on before.

866
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:39,360
You can't wait until it's time to sign

867
00:40:39,640 --> 00:40:41,000
and then jack up the price.

868
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:42,640
The Xuan family does business

869
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:44,920
not by breaking rules like this, right?

870
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:47,440
We Xuans do play by the rules.

871
00:40:47,440 --> 00:40:49,200
What you just said makes sense.

872
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:52,040
Mr. Du, may I cut in here?

873
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:55,240
Do you know Jiang Erhu?

874
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:01,360
Why are you asking about him?

875
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:02,680
I don't know him.

876
00:41:03,560 --> 00:41:04,360
Is that so?

877
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:06,440
Last night, Jiang Erhu

878
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:08,760
did go to your hotel to see you.

879
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:09,880
Think again.

880
00:41:13,280 --> 00:41:14,560
You've probably got the wrong person.

881
00:41:14,560 --> 00:41:15,840
I don't know him.

882
00:41:16,080 --> 00:41:18,200
I came all this way out here.

883
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:21,640
Uncle Xuan, aren't you sincere about selling?

884
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:29,640
Mr. Xuan,

885
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:33,800
my offer is twelve million.

886
00:41:35,640 --> 00:41:39,920
Actually, it's not about how much money.

887
00:41:40,160 --> 00:41:42,680
We Xuans value heritage above all.

888
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:46,280
Whether making Xuan paper or being a person,

889
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:49,960
honesty and integrity come first.

890
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:51,920
That's also a Xuan family rule.

891
00:41:59,000 --> 00:41:59,840
Uncle Xuan.

892
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:01,560
Fine, fine, I'll sign.

893
00:42:08,840 --> 00:42:09,640
Master!

894
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:17,000
Master, wait for me.

895
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:17,800
Don't sign yet.

896
00:42:18,520 --> 00:42:19,360
Hey.

897
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:23,960
I have to sign too.

898
00:42:24,480 --> 00:42:25,640
I have to take a careful look.

899
00:42:28,680 --> 00:42:30,120
Taozi just found out

900
00:42:30,280 --> 00:42:31,440
that among the twenty-two pending lawsuits

901
00:42:31,440 --> 00:42:32,960
Detian Company is currently facing,

902
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:34,720
All of them mention the name Jiang Xinming.

903
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:35,600
We suspect

904
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:37,680
he's the real controller behind Detian Company.

905
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:39,480
Go look him up right now.

906
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:40,600
Find out about him.

907
00:42:41,160 --> 00:42:43,600
He's the GM of Malaysia Planet Paper.

908
00:42:43,680 --> 00:42:44,720
Okay, got it.

909
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:50,080
Mr. Du, you said you don't know Jiang Erhu.

910
00:42:50,440 --> 00:42:53,400
But you surely know Jiang Xinming, right?

911
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:58,840
Isn't Jiang Xinming the son of Jiang Yousan?
